entry.title: [LCPP] preloading LCP candidate images with loading=lazy
entry.content:
This CL implements the preloading behavior to LCP candidate images,

which have loading="lazy" attributes behind the flag.



In theory loading="lazy" is added to the image located below the fold

for the loading start timing optimization. If the LCP image has the

attribute, that would negatively affect the metric.



This CL updates the preload scanner to create a preload request

regardless of whether the loading="lazy" attribute exists or not when

the image element is in the LCPP element locator.



In the future, we have an idea that extending this behavior to the JS

based custom lazy loading, but this CL starts from the native lazy

loading.

entry.content:
This CL adds parsing and serialization support of `ruby`, `ruby-base`

and `ruby-text` for `display` property values.

`inline`, and we should support `block ruby`.

New value are guarded by CssDisplayRuby flag, and the flag is off by

default now.

entry.title: Link Capturing: Enable app-to-app capturing for target="_blank" links
entry.content:
When App-to-App link capturing flags are enabled on ChromeOS, we allow

link clicks within an app window to link capture, even without the link

capturing user preference being enabled.



This is difficult for target="_blank" links clicked within a web app

window, which navigate within a regular browser tab, rather than in the

source app window. This means that link capturing code can't directly

tell whether a link was clicked inside an app window.



To make this work, we pass the source app ID from the browser navigator

into link capturing code via a TabHelper attached to the new web

contents. This allows the ID to be read later, inside a different

browser and possibly after multiple redirects.



Screen recording of behavior at https://crbug.com/1480903#c10

entry.title: Modify IconKey to move the `timeline` setting to AppService.
entry.content:
This CL is used to prepare for CL:4969258,



When the AppStorage is enabled, the publishers could publish a new icon

key with an increased `timeline`. That may caused icons refreshed

during the init phase adding apps for the first time.



This CL moves the icon key updates from publishers to AppService,

AppRegistryCache to prevent the icons refresh:

1. Remove `timeline` and `raw_icon_updated`, and add `update_version`

to specify the icon update info.

2. `update_version` should hold a bool to specify whether the icon image

is updated by the app when the publisher publishes the app.

`update_version` should never hold a int32_t when calling OnApps to publish apps.

3 AppRegistryCache generates an int32_t for `update_version` to notify

AppService clients whether reload the icon, when merging `deltas`.

`update_version` should never hold a bool in AppRegistryCache's

`states_`.

4. If the icon has a valid `resource_id`, `update_version` is

`kInvalidVersion` in AppRegistryCache's `states_`, and never changes.

5. When an app is added, if the icon doesn't have a valid `resource_id`,

`update_version` is set as `kInitVersion`.

6. `update_version` isn't changed if `icon_effects` is changed.

`update_version` is increased only when the app updates, or upgrades,

publish a new icon image.

7. The default value is set as false to ease the publishers implementation when calling OnApps.



Modify remote apps, to set `raw_icon_updated` as true when updating

icons to re-load icons.



Fix the bug in WebApkManagerTest.QueuesUpdatedApp. `updated_app_info`

is modified for `title` to make the app name change, but

InstallWebApp doesn't use the new updated `updated_app_info` as the

parameter. ( Without the icon key change in this CL, the icon key is

always updated since the timeline is increased.) So modify the test

code, to use the new `updated_app_info` to remove the dependency on the

icon key change.

change.

enforce that larger minimum size even after the dialog is closed.
